The paper is about a neural collaborative filtering model that uses self-attention, which is a technique commonly used in natural language processing (NLP) tasks. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are likely categories. Additionally, the model is a neural network, which falls under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper uses embeddings, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) tasks, making cs.CV a possible category as well.
